From 9cefe344f8ed8281816fcc45c09b0c9751d875b8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrey Kasaurov <andrey.kasaurov@amd.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 2026 01:36:43 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Mark compile-minimal-cached-bad-dir.cl as UNSUPPORTED on
 Windows

The test checks OS-specific error message text when the cache
directory is invalid. Windows produces a different error message
("Can't get a temporary file") than Linux ("Not a directory"),
causing the FileCheck to fail. The cache behavior itself is correct
on both platforms.
---
 .../cache-tests/compile-minimal-test-cached-bad-dir.cl        | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/amd/comgr/test-lit/cache-tests/compile-minimal-test-cached-bad-dir.cl b/amd/comgr/test-lit/cache-tests/compile-minimal-test-cached-bad-dir.cl
index df6aa7f068f8..81fa966c1fca 100644
--- a/amd/comgr/test-lit/cache-tests/compile-minimal-test-cached-bad-dir.cl
+++ b/amd/comgr/test-lit/cache-tests/compile-minimal-test-cached-bad-dir.cl
@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@
+// UNSUPPORTED: system-windows
 // RUN: export AMD_COMGR_CACHE=1
 //
 // COM: fail to create the cache, but still produce something valid
-- 
2.34.1

